        <div class="text-left lap-text-left tab-text-center mob-text-center">
          <h2 class="title ">
            
                      How to Profitably Scale AI Inference?
          
          </h2>
        </div>
       </div>
      
    

  
  </div>
<div class="nv-text text aem-GridColumn--tablet--12 aem-GridColumn--offset--tablet--0 aem-GridColumn--default--none aem-GridColumn--phone--none aem-GridColumn--phone--12 aem-GridColumn--tablet--none aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--7 aem-GridColumn--offset--phone--0 aem-GridColumn--offset--default--0">
 
 	
    <div id="nv-text-a4bb6b7f11" class="general-container-text            ">
			<div class="text-left lap-text-left tab-text-center mob-text-center">
				<div class="description ">
                	<p><span class="p--large">AI inference—how we experience AI through chatbots, copilots, and creative tools—is scaling at a double exponential pace. User adoption is accelerating while the AI tokens generated per interaction, driven by agentic workflows, long-thinking reasoning, and <a href="/glossary/mixture-of-experts/">mixture-of-experts</a> (MoE) models, soars in parallel.&nbsp;</span></p> 
<p><span class="p--large">To enable inference at this massive scale, NVIDIA delivers data-center-scale architecture on an annual rhythm. Our extreme hardware and software codesign delivers order-of-magnitude leaps in performance and drives down the cost per token, making advanced AI experiences economically viable at scale.</span></p> 
<p><span class="p--large">NVIDIA GB300 NVL72 delivers 50x tokens per watt and 35x lower token cost over Hopper™, maximizing revenue within the same power budget and driving higher profit margins. Continuous software optimizations extract maximum performance at chip, rack, and data center scale, further improving return on investment over time.</span></p>
                </div>
			</div>
	</div>

    

</div>

    
